43:26.633 --> 43:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The Chautauqua
Auditorium in Boulder, Colorado
recently, at the start of

43:33.600 --> 43:38.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a new tour by two musicians
who've been doing this a long
time, but never together.

43:42.666 --> 43:47.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And while it's called the
blues, 75-year-old Taj Mahal and
65-year-old Keb' Mo' are feeling

43:49.300 --> 43:50.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
nothing but joy.

43:50.800 --> 43:52.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TAJ MAHAL, Musician: That's
what we like about music.

43:52.533 --> 43:56.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's why we do music,
to share the fun.

43:56.666 --> 43:59.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Life brings a lot of strife.

43:59.500 --> 44:01.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
In the digital age,
it's even more intense.

44:01.433 --> 44:04.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And a lot of people don't
know how to get loose of it.

44:04.833 --> 44:09.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, our job as musicians is to
help them get loose and have a
good time and feel good about

44:11.500 --> 44:13.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
themselves.

44:13.533 --> 44:17.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Born Henry Saint
Clair Fredericks, Taj Mahal is
a living legend in the world

44:19.433 --> 44:23.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of roots and blues music, a
singer-songwriter who plays
many instruments and draws from

44:24.366 --> 44:29.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
many musical influences.

44:31.300 --> 44:35.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Kevin Moore, Keb' Mo''s
given name, spent many
years in various R&amp;B,
rock, and pop bands,

44:37.700 --> 44:41.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
until he went out on his own
in the early 1990s and focused
on his first love, the blues,

44:43.466 --> 44:46.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
gaining renown as
a master guitarist,
singer, and songwriter.

44:46.733 --> 44:51.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KEB' MO', Musician: It was
like a missing piece that
made everything relevant.

44:51.666 --> 44:56.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, what I did was, I took all
of those things that I had been
doing before, those experiences,

44:58.366 --> 45:02.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
took the blues and
wrapped it in there.

45:02.233 --> 45:07.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And what came out was Keb' Mo'.

45:09.800 --> 45:14.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Now, together,
they are TajMo, the name of
their new album, which features

45:17.800 --> 45:22.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
several songs they co-wrote,
including "Don't Leave Me Here."

45:31.566 --> 45:36.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On "Take a Giant Step," one
of Taj Mahal's earlier songs,
they were joined on stage by

45:37.166 --> 45:41.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
his daughters.

45:43.666 --> 45:47.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then there was the more raw
acoustic duet of "Diving Duck
Blues," a song that Taj Mahal

45:53.566 --> 45:58.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
first recorded on his
debut album back in 1968.

46:00.600 --> 46:05.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have heard you for a long
time, blues, folk, world

46:16.766 --> 46:20.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
music, I mean, different
kinds of elements, different
kind of influences.

46:20.600 --> 46:22.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TAJ MAHAL: My grandparents
come from the Caribbean.

46:22.666 --> 46:26.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I grew up listening to Caribbean
music, as much as I listened
to the Southern gospel.

46:26.500 --> 46:28.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
My dad liked bebop.

46:28.433 --> 46:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We had bebop and jazz, and
jump blues, you know, and
spirituals, and classical music,

46:34.766 --> 46:36.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
opera, everything, you know?

46:36.600 --> 46:40.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, it's like it didn't
hurt me because I
heard all those things.

46:40.866 --> 46:45.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It didn't take away from -- if
I heard a real deep blues song,
I don't care how much ragtime

46:46.966 --> 46:49.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I listen to, that
song's going to get me.

46:49.366 --> 46:53.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's going to get somebody
else too, if they get
a chance to hear it.

46:53.200 --> 46:58.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
KEB' MO': It's a
beautiful -- the beauty
in it is just so deep.

47:00.133 --> 47:02.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I heard the old Muddy
Waters stuff, but, wait a
minute, now, that's what it is.

47:02.466 --> 47:06.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I could feel the slave
ship coming over the ocean.

47:06.566 --> 47:08.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
TAJ MAHAL: Yes.

47:08.033 --> 47:10.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KEB' MO': I could feel the
Jim Crow, the cotton-picking.

47:10.100 --> 47:14.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I could feel the sense of
pride welling up in a man out
of his own circumstances, that

47:17.033 --> 47:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he had to rise up out of a
challenging circumstance of
Jim Crow and slavery and stuff.

47:22.866 --> 47:25.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I hear all of that.

47:25.066 --> 47:27.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that resonates universally.

47:27.166 --> 47:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But what you
two have managed to do is make
a life of this, right, without

47:34.166 --> 47:35.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
worrying about
the commercialism?

47:35.166 --> 47:37.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KEB' MO': Yes, commercialism.

47:37.233 --> 47:41.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's something working in
life and in the universe in the
bigger picture that has nothing

47:42.433 --> 47:45.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to do with commerce and money.

47:45.033 --> 47:50.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, for me, I found that after
20 years going after money, that
the faster I ran after money,

47:53.633 --> 47:55.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the faster the money ran.

47:55.533 --> 47:56.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

47:56.533 --> 47:57.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Right.

47:57.533 --> 47:58.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That sounds like a blues song.

47:58.933 --> 48:01.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TAJ MAHAL: Yes, yes, the
faster I run after the money...

48:01.833 --> 48:03.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

48:03.900 --> 48:07.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KEB' MO': And so I finally
just got out of breath and
stopped -- stopped running.

48:13.233 --> 48:14.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

48:14.866 --> 48:16.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: And, of
course, neither of them
has stopped playing.

48:16.500 --> 48:19.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Together, the sound
they're creating is both
upbeat and uplifting.

48:19.633 --> 48:23.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAJ MAHAL: Did we know
what it was going to
sound like at this point?

48:23.366 --> 48:24.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
No.

48:24.833 --> 48:26.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But we knew that it was
going to be something good.

48:26.300 --> 48:27.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Yes, we knew it was going
to be something good.

48:27.600 --> 48:29.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I mean, it could have
gone the other way too.

48:29.233 --> 48:31.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I could have said,
Moore, get out of here.

48:31.700 --> 48:32.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

48:32.933 --> 48:37.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KEB' MO': That's what
I thought might happen.

48:39.800 --> 48:41.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

48:41.800 --> 48:45.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: As always,
there's the question of how long
the blues will live on and who

48:47.166 --> 48:49.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
will take up the mantle.

48:49.333 --> 48:54.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Taj Mahal and Keb' Mo' are
supremely confident the music
will take care of itself.

48:54.033 --> 48:56.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KEB' MO': Taking on the blues
is a big responsibility.

48:56.733 --> 48:59.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So I understand why
people would be concerned.

48:59.166 --> 49:03.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But the music and riches
is about happiness.

49:03.133 --> 49:04.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The blues will be fine.

49:04.800 --> 49:06.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAJ MAHAL: Disciples?

49:06.300 --> 49:10.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
